H0.text: Which letter of the Greek alphabet when written looks like a capital P . Beta (Β)

H1.text: Which letter of the Greek alphabet when written looks like a capital P . Gamma (Γ)

H2.text: Which letter of the Greek alphabet when written looks like a capital P . Delta (Δ)

H3.text: Which letter of the Greek alphabet when written looks like a capital P . Ρ

A4.text: Its uppercase form uses the same glyph, Ρ, as the distinct Latin letter P; the two letters have different Unicode encodings.
